    {
      "id": "PopularPost119100",
      "post_content": "This card provides the same amount of card advantage over your opponent that [Counsel of the Soratami](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counsel of the Soratami)/[Divination](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Divination) does, for the same CMC. Now, I guess it is more restrictive - this isn't true if your opponent's hand is empty, and I'm not sure that it's true if you're in a multiplayer game - but it's an interesting way to look at the card.\n  \n   \nCounsel and Divination seem to be pretty universally reviled for being bad, but I'd say that 2 cards for 3 is reasonable - they have yet to print something that gets you 2 cards for 2 with no drawback. If card advantage +1 for 3 is fair in blue, then couldn't you say that the card advantage +1 for 3 is actually ***good*** in black?\n  \n   \nPutting aside my understanding (*or misunderstanding*) of the concept of card advantage, as I've mentioned on [Mind Ravel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=2471), there are precious few cantrip effects on discard spells. [Brainbite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainbite) upgrade... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Leshrac_Nightwalker",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost119100\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">This card provides the same amount of card advantage over your opponent that <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Counsel of the Soratami\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counsel of the Soratami\">Counsel of the Soratami</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Divination\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Divination\">Divination</a> does, for the same CMC.  Now, I guess it is more restrictive - this isn't true if your opponent's hand is empty, and I'm not sure that it's true if you're in a multiplayer game - but it's an interesting way to look at the card.  \r<br/> <br/>Counsel and Divination seem to be pretty universally reviled for being bad, but I'd say that 2 cards for 3 is reasonable - they have yet to print something that gets you 2 cards for 2 with no drawback.  If card advantage +1 for 3 is fair in blue, then couldn't you say that the card advantage +1 for 3 is actually <i><b>good</b></i> in black?  \r<br/> <br/>Putting aside my understanding (<i>or misunderstanding</i>) of the concept of card advantage, as I've mentioned on <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"2471\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=2471\">Mind Ravel</a>, there are precious few cantrip effects on discard spells.  <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Brainbite\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainbite\">Brainbite</a> upgrade... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 119100)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '119100'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy2435\">Leshrac_Nightwalker</span>\r\n                                (11/30/2010 9:26:06 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
