    {
      "id": "PopularPost315945",
      "post_content": "Outside of dedicated discard decks, a few discard cards can be useful to knock that last card out of your opponent's hand that they were saving for a rainy day. As far as options for that slot go, this is decent. (Sure, [Funeral Charm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Funeral Charm) is more versatile and has the instant speed benefit, but it can also potentially be a, heh, dead card. This never will be since it at worst burns a bit of mana, which is preferable to being useless)",
      "posted_by": "LordRandomness",
